Lowvelders came in their numbers to take part in the annual International Yoga Day at the Lowveld Botanical Garden on Saturday morning, June 11. Coordinated by Kanniah Srini and family and sponsored by the Consulate of India, locals gathered at the Garden with their towels and yoga mats at 09:00.  With around 150 people in attendance, the event was led by well-known yoga instructor, Maya Bhatt. ALSO READ: Valencia community stands united to repair potholes  The early morning sunshine and cool breeze made great weather for the attendees to practise their yoga. Following the event, the guests were treated to some fresh bananas and oranges and cool drinks sponsored by Spar.  International Yoga Day is officially held on June 21, with the theme being “Yoga for Humanity”.       